#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.94:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga"
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Saradasutta"
msgstr "94. Springtime"

# Saradasamaya is between the vassa and the hema. Since it’s before the cold it can be considered as “autumn”. But autumn conveys a distinct set of connotations. What is evoked here is the clear skies that follow the rainy season, a familiar and refreshing experience to one living in such climates.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.94:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve ādicco "
"nabhaṃ abbhussakkamāno sabbaṃ ākāsagataṃ tamagataṃ abhivihacca bhāsate ca "
"tapate ca virocati ca."
msgstr ""
"“After the rainy season the sky is clear and cloudless. And when the sun "
"rises, it dispels all the darkness from the sky as it shines and glows and "
"radiates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: uppajjati → udapādi (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an3.94:2.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yato ariyasāvakassa virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ "
"uppajjati, saha dassanuppādā, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa tīṇi saṃyojanāni "
"pahīyanti—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the stainless, immaculate vision of the teaching "
"arises in a noble disciple, three fetters are given up:"

msgctxt "an3.94:2.2"
msgid "sakkāyadiṭṭhi, vicikicchā, sīlabbataparāmāso."
msgstr "identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.94:3.1"
msgid "Athāparaṃ dvīhi dhammehi niyyāti abhijjhāya ca byāpādena ca."
msgstr "Afterwards they get rid of two things: desire and aversion."

msgctxt "an3.94:3.2"
msgid ""
"So vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ "
"vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, "
"they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected."

#. VAR: taṃ → tassa (mr)
#. VAR: puna imaṃ → punayimaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an3.94:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tasmiñce, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako kālaṃ kareyya, natthi taṃ saṃyojanaṃ "
"yena saṃyojanena saṃyutto ariyasāvako puna imaṃ lokaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If that noble disciple passed away at that time, they’re bound by no fetter "
"that might return them to this world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.94:3.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
